---
import ConditionPage from '../../components/ConditionPage.astro';
---
<ConditionPage
	title="Treatment in Clapham"
	highlight="Balance & Dizziness"
	heroSubtitle="Feeling unsteady or dizzy can affect your confidence, your movement, and your day-to-day life. We help you feel stable and in control again."
	breadcrumb="Balance & Dizziness"
	seoTitle="Balance & Dizziness Treatment in Clapham"
	seoDescription="Expert balance and dizziness treatment in Clapham, London. Vestibular rehab and targeted physio to reduce symptoms and rebuild your confidence."
	introImage="/condition/balance-and-dizziness/skateboard-balance.jpg"
	whoImage="/condition/balance-and-dizziness/inner-ear-model.jpg"
	intro={[
		"Feeling unsteady or dizzy can affect your confidence, your movement, and your day-to-day life. At Balance Performance Physiotherapy, we look at what's really driving your symptoms.",
		"Whether your dizziness is linked to the inner ear, your balance system, or how your body processes movement, we'll help you feel more stable and in control again.",
	]}
	symptomsHeading="When to get it"
	symptomsHighlight="checked"
	symptomsIntro="It's worth coming in for an assessment if you're experiencing any of the following:"
	symptomsList={[
		"A spinning sensation or vertigo, especially when changing position",
		"Feeling unsteady when walking or turning",
		"Dizziness triggered by head movement or busy environments",
		"Loss of confidence with balance or fear of falling",
		"Difficulty focusing or feeling disorientated",
		"Ongoing symptoms following illness or infection",
	]}
	treatmentHeading="How we treat"
	treatmentHighlight="balance & dizziness"
	treatmentIntro="We combine targeted rehabilitation with movement-based therapy to retrain your balance system and reduce symptoms. Your plan may include:"
	treatmentList={[
		"Physiotherapy to improve coordination and movement control",
		"Vestibular rehabilitation exercises to retrain the inner ear and balance system",
		"Gradual exposure to movement to reduce sensitivity and build confidence",
		"Balance training to improve stability and reduce fall risk",
		"Advice on managing symptoms in day-to-day life",
	]}
	whoHeading="Who we"
	whoHighlight="help"
	whoList={[
		"Seniors looking to improve balance and reduce fall risk",
		"People recovering from inner ear conditions or illness",
		"Individuals with ongoing dizziness affecting daily life",
		"Neurological patients needing specialist balance rehabilitation",
		"Active individuals experiencing dizziness during exercise",
		"Anyone who feels less confident moving due to instability",
	]}
	faqs={[
		{ q: "What causes dizziness and balance problems?", a: "They are often linked to the inner ear, but can also involve the brain or how your body processes movement and position." },
		{ q: "What is vestibular physiotherapy?", a: "It's a specialist approach that retrains your balance system using targeted exercises to reduce dizziness and improve stability." },
		{ q: "Is it safe to move if I feel dizzy?", a: "Yes, when guided properly. Movement is often a key part of recovery, and we progress this in a controlled way." },
		{ q: "Do I need a referral?", a: "No, you can book directly with us for an assessment." },
		{ q: "Will I get exercises to do at home?", a: "Yes. You'll be given simple, specific exercises to support your recovery between sessions." },
	]}
/>
